You know what REALLY confused me when I first wanted to learn Git? I thought you had to be a seasoned programmer to get any use out of it. 

Actually though, it's the perfect tool for any collaborative project, whether it be a website or a novel. It'd be a great tool for a writer and editor to use together, for example.

These are my tips, tricks, and thoughts about using Git and Github, in .txt form. They're helping me collect my thoughts for an explainer article. 